cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with learning robust classifiers in the presence of noisy data, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of semantic relations between classes, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category. Finally, the paper also mentions remote sensing image semantic segmentation, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
